jt-pve-storage-netapp (0.1.6-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Full Clone Support Release
  * New Feature: Full Clone from VM Snapshot
    - Clone a VM from any specific snapshot to create independent VM
    - Uses temporary FlexClone for snapshot data access
    - Automatic cleanup of temporary FlexClones (1 hour expiry)
    - Works with both iSCSI and FC protocols
  * New Feature: Full Clone from Current State
    - Full Clone of running or stopped VMs
    - PVE/qemu-img reads directly from current volume
  * Technical Implementation:
    - path() creates temporary FlexClone when snapshot access needed
    - Temporary FlexClone LUN automatically mapped to igroup
    - State tracking in /var/run/pve-storage-netapp-temp-clones.json
    - Cleanup runs automatically during storage status checks
  * New API Methods:
    - volume_is_splitting(): Check if clone split is in progress
    - volume_wait_clone_split(): Wait for clone split to complete
  * Linked Clone Improvement:
    - Linked Clone from template now stays space-efficient (no auto-split)
  * Storage Deactivation:
    - deactivate_storage now properly cleans up iSCSI sessions
    - Flushes device buffers and removes multipath devices
    - Logs out from iSCSI targets when storage is disabled/removed
    - Safety check: skips cleanup for devices still in use
  * Bug Fixes:
    - Fixed list_images incorrectly showing FlexClones as templates
    - Fixed igroup name lookup in temp FlexClone creation
    - Fixed wait_for_multipath_device parameter format
    - Added retry logic for stale has_flexclone metadata during template deletion
  * Documentation Updates:
    - Updated installation SOP with multipath.conf configuration
    - Added security documentation (password storage, API permissions)
    - Added ONTAP account setup options (Cluster vs SVM level)

