jt-pve-storage-netapp (0.1.4-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * FC SAN Support Release
  * New Feature: Fibre Channel (FC) SAN Protocol Support
    - New configuration option: ontap-protocol (iscsi|fc)
    - Automatic FC HBA WWPN discovery from /sys/class/fc_host
    - FC igroup creation with 'fcp' protocol
    - Support for multiple FC HBA ports per node
    - FC LIP (Loop Initialization Primitive) for LUN rescan
  * New Module: FC.pm
    - get_fc_wwpns(): Get all FC HBA port WWPNs
    - is_fc_available(): Check if FC HBA exists
    - rescan_fc_hosts(): Trigger FC and SCSI rescan
    - format_wwn(): Convert WWN to standard format
  * Robustness Improvements:
    - Concurrent disk allocation now retries with next available ID
    - Aggregate validation on storage activation
    - Configurable device discovery timeout (ontap-device-timeout)
    - Improved error messages with actionable hints
  * Performance Improvements:
    - Batch LUN query in list_images (reduces API calls significantly)
  * Bug Fixes:
    - Fixed path() and snapshot_rollback to support FC protocol
    - Fixed protocol-aware device rescanning throughout codebase
    - Fixed async job handling for DELETE and PATCH API calls
    - Volume deletion now properly waits for ONTAP job completion
    - Fixed template (base-xxx-disk-x) volume name handling
    - parse_volname now correctly returns isBase flag for templates
  * Compatibility:
    - FC and iSCSI use same multipath configuration
    - FC and iSCSI use same WWID-based device identification
    - Existing iSCSI configurations continue to work (default protocol)
  * Documentation:
    - Added FC SAN configuration examples
    - Updated CONFIGURATION.md with ontap-protocol option

